are both more complex and multifaceted than they are often recognized to be. By including both historical processes (the development of Chinese funerals in late imperial Beijing or the refashioning of memorial commemoration in the wake of the Vietnam war) and particular events (the visit of Pope John Paul II to shared shrines in Sri Lanka or the Al-Qaeda bombing of an ancient Jewish synagogue on the Island of Djerba in Tunisia), the volume demonstrates the importance of understanding the wider contexts within which social interactions take place and shows that tolerance and intercommunalism are simultaneously possible and perpetually under threat.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aPilgrims and pilgrimages. 0aReligionsxRelations. 0aSacred space. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aAlbera, Dionigi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBastin, Rohan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBigelow, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoum, Aomar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowman, Glenn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowman, Glenn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarpenter-Latiri, Dora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChau, Adam Yuet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCouroucli, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKwon, Heonik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTuladhar-Douglas, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z97